cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with algorithms for counting triangulations and pseudo-triangulations of a set of points in the plane, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of running times, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of divide-and-conquer and sweep line paradigms suggests that it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), respectively.
